WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:13.360
Hey everyone, my name is J.J. Allaire. I work at RStudio and I'm here today to talk about

00:00:13.360 --> 00:00:19.320
a new scientific and technical publishing system called Quarto and then specifically

00:00:19.320 --> 00:00:27.600
how Quarto can be used with Julia. So a little bit of a road map. I'll cover first what is

00:00:27.600 --> 00:00:33.560
Quarto, where does it fit among other projects you might use or be aware of. Talk a little

00:00:33.560 --> 00:00:38.840
bit about the concept of scientific markdown, which is an important thing that underpins

